{
  "texts": [
    "Not all of the v15 improvement can be attributed to alignment, because the 2D section images for v15 were reworked to remove montaging errors in v14.",
    "However, only a small fraction of total area (<1%) was directly affected by montaging errors.",
    "Moreover, most montaging errors occurred around tissue boundary, while our evaluation shows that v15 specifically outperforms v14 at correction of discontinuous defects inside the tissue (Fig. 5b, Supplementary Fig.",
    "As an additional effort to isolate the improvements due to alignment rather than montaging, we evaluated another FAFB alignment (v14.1) that was previously released 31.",
    "v14.1 was created by applying a preliminary version of our pipeline (Methods) to v14 images, so that montaging errors in v14 were \"baked in\" and could not be corrected."
  ]
}